div.p:
We conclude that the individuals who are on top in Ethiopia today may disappear, even within the year, but:
—in any case, some element of the military will continue to dominate the power structure, probably still identified as the Provisional Military Advisory Council (PMAC);
—the revolution will not be reversed to restore the old political order;
—the PMAC, in its impatience to get on with reform, is likely to continue to resort to coercion, thereby inviting opposition;
—at the same time, however, the PMAC may try to gain some degree of political legitimacy by erecting a facade of civilian institutions.
